Dogs are called “man’s best friend”, and with good cause. They are loving friends who provide families with happiness and pleasure. However, even the most affectionate dog may snap or bite when provoked. Young children are particularly at risk of dog bites, with those aged between five and nine most at risk. Most dog bites are caused by a dog that the victim knows, such as a friend, neighbour, or even their own family pet. Parents and caregivers must discuss how children should behave around dogs to prevent bites. Here are some tips: The above has been adapted from Society for the Prevention of Animal Cruelty